And here I go to one of my biggest lessons of this year! We often read a line that goes ‚Äúin order to find yourself you have to loose yourself first‚Äù we often read it but to understand the depth of that statement you have to find yourself in that situation. The truth is we get lost every day and every day we find ourselves again, of course some days in higher levels than others! Traveling is a healthy way to loose yourself! Exposing yourself to different landscapes, cultures, peoples, ways of thinking, makes you feel a little lost, but constantly finding yourself with the vibrations that resonate with your soul, you don‚Äôt need a big tragedy to accurately find yourself, your purpose and your drive to execute it! You need exposure and an open mind! Eventually, like a puzzle... pieces start to fit together and the joy of living start becoming greater and greater üôèüèº

By adding the load in a vertical fashion in the overhead bulgarian squat makes the movement hip dominant. In order to haver a full ROM you will be forced to engage your glutes. For the split stance deadlift the hex bar distributes the load better rather than having a barbell in front of you, if you want to get more glute out of the deadlift, at least this bar does that for me give it a try, and let me know what you guys think!

As this year comes to an end I‚Äôm starting to see posts about how 2020 is going to be the year of_____ fill in the blank. If you really want to have a successful year you have to start now and get ahead of everyone that will be competing in your field. One thing @luisenriquepzia has taught me over our years of relationship and business together, Is to always evaluate where we are, what we are doing wrong and what have we done correctly?
We take December to do that, and I encourage you to do the same. If you wanna have a really successful year. Start isolating the areas of your life that are important to you. Mine are these 5:
Professional life
Love life
Family
Friendships
Health (mental, physical, spiritual).
-
After isolating them start by discarding the distractions around them! Visualize the big picture, and start dividing it into small goals and step that you will use towards achieving that goal. Once you‚Äôve organized that you shall realize that many things you are investing time and energy on are just distractions! Time, right alongside health is the biggest currency you have in life! How you invest both of these into your purpose will dictate how you will fulfill your life. Your life Is either going to be a happy beautiful journey, or you will be miserable on your way to trying to achieve it!
It‚Äôs your responsibility, your duty, your job to  actively work towards your goals! And you only have two options around it! Either stay actively working to make the journey a joyful one or a miserable one!
-
If the choice is to make it a joyful one! Discipline is your biggest ally, because sometimes happiness is about having the discipline to stay the course and do the things you know will help you even if in that moment you don‚Äôt feel like doing them!
-

A frequent ask questions i get is the following: ‚Äúcan i look like you training at home?‚Äù Or ‚Äúcan I improve my physique training at home?‚Äù.

So I‚Äôll answer both right here. First of all I didn‚Äôt build my physique with home workouts. I apply them to when im traveling or with a super busy schedule and I rather save some time avoiding the trip to the gym. They help me maintain my shape year round!.
-
In order to create progress with home workouts, you will need to find ways to make your workouts more intense as your body adapts and progress to the work load you been training to. Here is where bands, tempos, time under tension, drop sets, And any other technique or tool you can apply to make your workouts more challenging as your make progress.

Whatever goal you have set for yourself, social media related or not! Regardless of where you start from the bottom or with help! To achieve success and to keep it will demand a consistently high work ethic! And the best possible organization you can have for your task!
-
The work ethic comes from our education, upbringings, and drive to succeed! That part I can only encourage you to always be better and improve around it!
However, when organization comes to play please establish your priorities clearly. 
In my case my top priority will always be every client I have training with me!
I have set up alarms to check my emails and communications with them!
Then I have my corporate relationships, sponsorships, collaborations, and publications.
With this part my husband helps me a lot since he used to be a lawyer and is aware of what‚Äôs right and fair concerning legalities. 
Now bringing my husband up leads to the topic of having a support system! Whatever you are trying to achieve, make sure to research and utilize all potential outlets of guidance. 
You will need to build a team of people going in the same direction and are as hungry as you are for it! This will create safety for your organization.
